translated: Hugoson, Gustav Helge, district veterinarian, Vetlanda, b. March 30, 1896 in Linde parish, Örebro county, son of Hugo Larsson and Maria Andersson. Married in 1929 to Brita Selin. Children: Birgitta b. 1930, Göran b. 1933. Completed high school in Lindesberg in 1911, studied at Karolinska High School in Örebro 1914, at Uppsala University 1914-1916, at the Veterinary College 1916-1925, received a degree in veterinary medicine in 1922 and became a licensed veterinarian in 1925. Held various positions in Finspång, Linköping, Tjällmo, and Kopparberg from 1924-1929, district veterinarian in Jokkmokk in 1929, the same position in Röksberg the same year, and in Vetlanda since 1931, acting inspection veterinarian in Vetlanda and Sävsjö. Member of the Board of the Vetlanda Red Cross district since 1941, its vice chairman from 1941-1943 and chairman since 1943, member of the board of L Jönköping Red Cross district since 1946, full member in the Red Cross since the same year, member of the local board of Vetlanda Samrealskola since 1945, board member of Småland Vänner and chairman of the local committee for Europe Assistance in 1946. Traveled to Germany, Switzerland, Hungary and other countries in 1937, 1938 and 1939, represented Sweden in Germany for the Red Cross in 1947. Wrote articles in newspapers and magazines.
